text: ·  TR. Bottom third is toughest part.  Top is a jug haul

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Hard boulder start, needed to get feet under. Defo height dependent. Then lots of little crimps, know the beta and move feet. Tick tac! Get above the fourth bolt and it’s a ladder.
·  Lead / Onsight. grabbed the first draw bc i didn’t have a stick clip but sent every move first try otherwise… whatever! super fun
·  Lead / Onsight. Could be 10d? Or maybe I'm strong
·  Lead / Redpoint. Got the send on my second time up.  Not too bad once I knew the beta. After the third clip it gets easier. The top is pretty juggy. A bit pumpy but not too bad

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Went up this and took by the first clip. Went up and took an unexpected fall by the third bolt when my foot popped. My first real big unexpected fall. Totally clean tho. Figured out the beta so I went up again for the send
·  Lead / Redpoint. I misread the opening moves, overlooking the left facing flake, blowing what would otherwise be an easy flash. Perhaps a bit soft for 11 though.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Fell three times trying to clip at the crux. Reachy for a crimp, had to use an intermediate hold. Start was a high foot boulder problem, basically required a one arm pull-up

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Led with Tiff belay after she set it up. Fun and rewarding, turns into plates at the top but burnt myself out getting through the crux moves down low. Grabbed the draw at the Crux move and then climbed back down to retry it. Took a few falls at the plates too due to pump / overgripping. Saw some people who sent the route to the left struggle on the same parts so would love to get on that sometime too.
·  Lead. My first ever lead 5.11!!! Woo!! First few clips were scary, took 3 takes. Then smooth sailing
· Have done a few times over the years
·  Lead / Redpoint. Tough clip 3 then smooth sailing
·  Lead / Redpoint. Start was thin but way better than I remembered! Love this route— definitely stiff off the ground but progressively easier as you go.
·  TR. got halfway up but hands gave up!
·  Lead / Onsight. I fell once, but I need to try again and I need to remember to do the 5:12 extension at the top next year

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Thin! But doable for sure. Two quick hangs while putting up draws. Fifth climb of the day and Didn’t try for the send but could have easily if I’d been fresher. Fun as hell and very sequency and cruxy to a great rest and relaxed upper portion.
·  Lead / Flash. Felt easier than it’s neighbor
·  Lead / Redpoint. saw a guy whip and fall upside down and smack his head on the wall to get a severe concussion right before I got on the wall. added to the spook.
·  Lead / Redpoint. Start was hard, big left foot and got a right knee on to stand up. Pretty sustained up to Africa
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. take on first three? bolts. repeated on top rope with multiple takes
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Fell once at midpoint crux
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. David clipped the first two draws for me and I took once but otherwise felt good!
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Struggled again. Probably shouldn’t start with this route! With Mike, Miranda, and Dakota.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Did not get over the 2 no clip. Very crimpy and would need to talk time to work out
·  Lead / Flash. Saw Kaylee do the first half (crux)
·  Lead / Flash. Delicate crimp dance for the first 4 clips
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Need to figure out roof; deep finger buckets below 5th clip
·  Lead / Flash. superb, slab crux start leads to perfect, reachy vertical crimp climbing, so good. stop sandbagging Caroline on reachy climbs you dickhead
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Top rope to 3rd bolt, lead after
·  Lead / Pinkpoint. First time through just working the moves,  sent second attempt
·  Lead / Redpoint. Agree with the consensus, feels soft for 11a

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Left side pull / undercling to start is a little tricky. Have feet out left to counter. Then RH will go to deeper hold. 

Around bolt 2-3 traverse right, and LH holds the side sloper while RH goes to the crimp and then clip from that. After that it should be easy.
·  TR. The start pumped me. Hard to figure out how to get my feet up when so extended to reach good ledge above roof. Climbed it pumped and it felt miserable.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. good route! pumped after a good morning of climbing, so crimped out mid-way up
·  Lead / Onsight. 11.b on the tag. Seemed a little soft. When super comfortable. Start is the crux.

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Tried this twice (?) and ripped left index pad the second time. Just around the third bolt shifting weight left to catch crimp with left hand. Tricky start too. Interesting movement for sure
·  Lead / Redpoint. Went up again for the send. Find crimps close to the first bolt to pull up onto. Shake out at second bolt. Climbing eases up to 10a around the 5th bolt. Fun!
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. 1 hang at Boulder problem and 1 take at third bolt
·  TR. Hung once, but definitely a very doable 11a for the future on lead
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Hung at bolt 1 - Numb fingers!!
·  Lead / Onsight. Pretty fun climbing after bolt 3. Crux is the weirdly slabby start.

·  TR. Did not finish - first half HARD for short people. 
Not my favorite climb
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. almost onsight very hot when i did it blew off a good crimp
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. A few attempts to get past first bolt; take at the crux

·  Lead / Flash. Lol, “go for that right jug” while looking up from the ground, at the third bolt.
First time on it and it was not a jug! Scary clipping position on thin crimp.
·  Lead / Redpoint. Super fun route, in the heat it felt 5.11 but overall long reaches on smaller holds

·  Lead / Redpoint. Easier for taller people
Give a brush before flash
Solid crimps, great movement
Keep high feet
Rewarded for low crux at end
·  TR. Donnie belayed me. Hard, but worth it
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. DNF. Forgot a lot of beta and the holds were wet. Had to cheat to get past the crux just above the third bolt.

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. First attempt of the day: Bolt-to-bolted to the 4th bolt, then finished the route. Second: One fall at the third bolt, then finished. Third: Fell at the third bolt a few times and took at the fourth bolt, then finished.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Bolt-to-bolted to the fourth(?) bolt, then finished the route.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. One hang bit great route
·  Lead / Redpoint. Felt super good and secure
·  Lead. Crimp with right hand at beginning. Fun sustained climb. Second 11a send
·  TR. Failed on this one. Got a quarter of the way up and got discouraged/scared and bailed
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. fell once, no other takes. great climb very satisfying. my favorite of the day. if I stayed to the left I probably would have onsighted it.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Jon lead this route
·  Follow. Love this climb.  Used a foot cam for the first time on the start.  The crimps are good.  Slightly thinner in the middle
·  TR. Much harder than it looks. Top section is really fun.

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Two massive attempts, the first one better than the second. Definitely needed to project the start- either mantle and high L hand or match with a high R and stand up. Sneaky R Gaston, long L reach to sidepull crimp. 

Second set of goes was a mess.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Had a lead fall but got up
·  Lead / Onsight. powerful mantle start to slab section using side pulls and crimps plate jugs to anchors!
·  Lead / Onsight. great route, definitely harder than momma Cindy, I agree with the muir 11b rating
·  Lead / Redpoint. 3rd go. Funnnn gym-like crimps!

·  Lead / Pinkpoint. Technical and crimpy, after crimp section it’s all jugs but figuring out crimp sequence took a bit. Beginning had a roofy start that’s fairly easy for me, with a fat left side pull. Good rest on it.
·  TR. Second attempt on it top roped to dial in beta. I got pumped out and hung on it
·  Lead / Flash. Hung out with Alex & Ben while they were working it. Fun climb on some good crimps.
·  TR. Fell at start would be scary lead but got rest of route
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Hung my way up but I could probably send this. Was mostly sketched clipping off small plates
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Grabbed bolt clipping 3rd, wack. Should’ve traversed left to better hold then clipped. Couple takes. Fun.
·  Lead / Flash. First 11 flash. Route is absolutely epic. Possibly my favorite in the red so far
·  Lead / Onsight. So good!! Quality climbing like Hideout routes. Easy climbing for the grade…after start sequence.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. hung due to pump :(
·  Lead / Onsight. onsighted while hanging draws

·  Lead / Flash. Easier pull from the "roof". Grab tiny crimps and side pulls to situate yourself early. Gets small and technical with your occasional sloped hold. Some razor crimps and delicate positions, but still a really fun route. The higher you go, the easier
·  Lead / Onsight. felt maybe 10c.... area is pretty soft
·  Lead / Onsight. Good stuff! Really fun and definitely the best route on the wall. Really good grippy incut crimps
·  Follow. tough roof start pull, 3rd to 4th bolt techy
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. First 11a!! Not clean but very fun movement, holds and all around good time. Last one of the day and I’m glad I did it!

·  Lead / Onsight. Pumpy overhang start into tender movements on half jugs for 4 bolts. Juggy finish with plenty of natural rests. 2 hard moves on the extension stopped me up, has a bail ring attached for the hopeful few.

·  Follow. Follow Carmen. Roof was ok using right heel hook, but fell trying to gain first bolt. Use the side pull and / or undercling to obtain balance. Rest is difficult pump crimp wondering mess to fight through.
·  Lead / Onsight. Blew a foot and almost lost it but kept it together for the send :)
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Missed a hold out left
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Too pumped to finish. Thin crimps, sustained until bolt 5, then easy.
·  Follow. Vaughn led harder first half— would have been a very unfun lead for me. Led second half, which is a fairly enjoyable plate haul
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Hard start but easy climbing after halfway
·  Follow. Thin edges. Crux is the bottom 3 draws.

·  Lead / Fell/Hung. cool route, quite varied in style. the lower section is quite challenging, and there's a crimp section that is tough. top is more like 5.10 climbing, but hard to do after all the pump. tried a second time on top rope, still hard!!
·  Lead / Onsight. Cool moves standing up through the Boulder problem to the first and second bolt. Interesting thin moves once you're on the face and then cruise the jugs to the top. Soft 11a

·  Lead / Pinkpoint. Pull a roof at the start (dyno if you’re short like me) then a couple balance moves from bolt 1 to 2. A this section at bolt 3 but good enough. And then easy 10a climbing to the chains. 
Fun route!
·  Lead / Flash. What a gem! Great climb - thin holds, but super positive and great movement. makes you think (in a good way!)
·  Lead / Redpoint. First time slipped at the first bolt and had to take. Came down and went right back up and sent it. Beautiful line. Sustained on crimpy holds. Good rests at the top
·  Follow. One fall, super crimpy til the top
·  Lead / Redpoint. One try, thanks Cal for hanging clips
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Close to the send. Dial in the start and fire through rest of sequences. Small crimps but they are more than enough
·  Lead / Onsight. better than momma cindy
· 2 pitches.  Lead / Redpoint. decked trying to clip first bolt. probably use a stick clip
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Crux is the first few bolts. Edges are tiny so move fast.
·  Lead / Redpoint. 2nd go. Blew flash after pulling roof start.
·  Lead / Fell/Hung. Got super pumped, fell and hung quite a bit
·  Lead / Redpoint. 2nd go. tried the extension but the fall was a tad sketch

· 2 pitches.  Lead / Redpoint. Fun and not pumpy with right beta. Clip 3rd bolt down low (not from thin pinch crimp). RH Lock off on pinch crimp and high LF to make left reach. Clip 4th bolt from jug 3 moves after RH bucket side pull. Chill after.
